1:Information:Information about this tool:xbian-info
2:Settings   :Change various system settings:
2.1:Base      :e.g. Resize SD, Overclocking, Hostname:
2.1.1:Resize SD   :Expand root partition to fill SD card:xbian-resizesd
2.1.2:Overclocking:Configure overclocking:changeoverclock
2.1.3:Hostname    :Change the default hostname:xbian-hostname
2.1.4:Timezone    :Set the default timezone:xbian-timezone
2.1.5:HDMI hotplug:Force HDMI to activate on boot:xbian-forcehdmi
2.2:User      :e.g. Change passwords:
2.2.1:XBian Password:Change password for xbian user:xbian-xbianpass
2.2.2:Root Password :Change password for root user:xbian-rootpass
2.3:Networking:e.g. LAN/WLAN Settings, SSH:
2.3.1:WLAN          :Configure wireless network connection:xbian-wlan
2.3.2:LAN           :Configure wired network connection:xbian-lan
2.3.3:SSH root login:Enable/Disable SSH root login:changesshroot 
3:Packages   :Install or remove additional packages:
3.1:Remote:Install packages from internet:remotepackages
3.2:Local :Install packages from *.tar.gz:remotepackages
4:Updates    :Check for XBian updates:notimplemented
